summary.purpose: Provides four coloured bicycle SVG icon generator functions (red, yellow, green, gray) conforming to the VehicleSvg signature for use as map markers and menu icons.
summary.problem_solved: Supplies the bicycle vehicle type's state-specific icon variants so map and menu components can reflect real-time state visually.

exports.name: redBicycleIcon
exports.description_one_line: Returns a red bicycle SVG element with configurable size, site colour, CSS class, and viewBox context.

exports.name: yellowBicycleIcon
exports.description_one_line: Returns a yellow bicycle SVG element with configurable size, site colour, CSS class, and viewBox context.

exports.name: greenBicycleIcon
exports.description_one_line: Returns a green bicycle SVG element with configurable size, site colour, CSS class, and viewBox context.

exports.name: grayBicycleIcon
exports.description_one_line: Returns a gray bicycle SVG element with configurable size, site colour, CSS class, and viewBox context.

symbols.name: redBicycleIcon
symbols.description_one_line: Returns a red bicycle SVG element with configurable size, site colour, CSS class, and viewBox context.

params.name: width
params.description: Width attribute for the SVG element.

params.name: height
params.description: Height attribute for the SVG element.

params.name: siteColor
params.description: Fill colour for site-specific colour accents.

params.name: className
params.description: CSS class name applied to the SVG element.

params.name: viewBoxFor
params.description: Context identifier ('map_icon' or 'menu_icon').

returns.description: Red bicycle icon SVG element. Red indicates ignition is off.

details.what_it_does: Generates a bicycle SVG icon in red, indicating the vehicle's ignition is off.

minimal_correct.title: Render a red bicycle icon
minimal_correct.code:
import { redBicycleIcon } from 'akeyless-assets-commons';

const icon = redBicycleIcon('30', '30', '#FF0000', 'newIconCar', 'map_icon');
